  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal money laundering prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Significant prison time (potentially years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional potential consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Frequency of offenses\n- Involvement in other criminal activities\n- Jurisdiction and specific laws\n\nProsecution is typically handled by federal agencies like the FBI and Department of Justice. Specific details can vary based on jurisdiction and individual case circumstances.",
